  "prompt": "Who pays for the cars on Top Gear?",
  "response": "On the television show \"Top Gear,\" the cars that are featured, tested, and reviewed are usually provided by the car manufacturers. These manufacturers often lend their vehicles to the show for promotional purposes, allowing the hosts to review and demonstrate them. In some cases, the BBC or the production company behind \"Top Gear\" may arrange to rent or borrow cars specifically for certain segments or challenges. The exact arrangements can vary depending on the specific episode and the types of cars being featured.",
